'''Tired and Emotional''' is a [[euphemism]] for "drunk". It was coined by the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[satire|satirical]] magazine [[Private Eye]] in [[1967]] in reference to [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] Cabinet minister [[George Brown, Baron George-Brown|George Brown]] but is now used as a stock phrase; the law of [[libel]] makes it unwise ever to directly refer to someone as drunk. It has become a widely used phrase outside the magazine.

